Prepared guitar - A prepared guitar is a guitar that has had its timbre altered by placing various objects on or between the instrument's strings, including other extended techniques.
Preparation time, time to prepare speeches in policy debate
Preparation (dental), the method by which a tooth is prepared when removing decay and designing a form that will provide adequate retention for a dental restoration
preparation definition: the action or process of making something ready for use or service or of getting ready for some occasion, test, or duty.
Prepared piano - A prepared piano is a piano that has had its sound altered by placing objects (preparations) between or on the strings or on the hammers or dampers.
Preparation (music), treatment of dissonance in tonal music
Preparedness - Preparedness refers to a very concrete research based set of actions that are taken as precautionary measures in the face of potential disasters.
